t m baehny chairman revenue chf  billion  operating income chf  million  profit chf  million  total assets chf  billion end  total equity chf  billion end  number of employees  end  website wwwgeberitcom geberit german pronunciation ˈɡəbeːrɪt or ˈɡəbeːʁɪt is a swiss multinational group specialized in manufacturing and supplying sanitary parts and related systems it is a leader in its field in europe with a global presence through its subsidiaries contents  history  the beginnings  expansion  strategy  product areas  sanitary systems  piping systems  bathroom ceramics  notes and references historyedit geberit headquarters the beginningsedit in  caspar melchior gebert started a plumbing business in rapperswil switzerland in  he began to manufacture parts his toilet tank the phoenix a first made of leadcoated wood and with lead fittings particularly a flushing mechanism was revolutionary and a great success when gebert died in  his sons albert and leo took over the business in the following years the company expanded within switzerland as well as to neighboring countries and added new products pipes taps and valves in the s the company was a pioneer of plastic parts in the sanitary industry the second world war affected the company but it soon recovered and in  introduced the first allplastic toilet tank made of polyethylene expansionedit in  heinrich and klaus gebert inherited control of the company and named it geberit the company opened a distribution subsidiary and new branches in europe which besides parts also offered technical services as germany was considered a growth market the first international subsidiary was opened there in  in pfullendorf which was also going to be the site of the first factory outside switzerland since then a number of subsidiaries were created in european countries including france  and austria  the company moved from rapperswil to a larger facility in rapperswiljona and introduced a concealed tank system in the s geberit introduced more new products such as full drainage systems flushmounted systems and new components for the hygiene sector a third plant was opened in  in pottenbrunnsankt pölten austria the company also created subsidiaries in denmark belgium and the netherlands the company made an attempt to enter the american market creating a subsidiary in michigan indiana however the us presence remained insignificant for years in  the company entered the installation systems market which went on to become the most important market of the company in  the german facilities were expanded and a warehouse complex was opened at its rapperswiljona headquarters it also acquired a big german player in the installationelements market sanbloc in  it began automating its production in  it acquired a stake in fae fluid air energy joining the fresh water supply systems sector in  the facilities of pottenbrunn were expanded in  a new plant was established in lichtenstein in eastern germany to take advantage of the new markets after the end of the cold war in  the gebert family withdrew from managing the company and the first outsider was appointed ceo of the company gunter f kelm the company continued its expansion with new facilities in rapperswiljona a factory for its mepla brand in givisiez and new international subsidiaries in italy and portugal in  the geberts sold geberit to the british private equity firm doughty hanson with the new cash the company started a series of acquisitions which included italys deriplast and walking pipe italiana germanys buchler werkzeugbau ag and the united kingdoms caradon terrain ltd in  the company opened its first production plant in china in june  geberit was listed on the swx swiss exchange in july  it raised its stake in fae fluid air energy to  percent with an agreement to take full control of fae by  in  the company suffered from the weakness of the german market but soon recovered in  it acquired a majority stake in the austrian company huter vorfertigung gmbh in july of that year with the aim of strengthen its position in the american market it purchased chicago faucet at a cost of  million dollars in  it purchased the leading german metal pipe manufacturer mapress holding from lindsay goldberg  bessemer at a cost of  million euros the geberit share was included in the swiss market index smi in  in  geberit acquired the finlandbased bath and toilet firm sanitec for  billion strategyedit the company manufactures and sells its products mainly under the geberit brand although some subsidiaries brands are also used it has operations in more than  countries geberit’s strategy rests on four pillars focus on sanitary technology commitment to innovation selective geographic expansion and continuous business process optimization for a number of years now geberit has been pursuing the threestage sales model and the pushpull strategy more specifically geberit products are distributed wholesale with the company training over  plumbers and decisionmakers a year at its  training centers around the world or at external training courses to date geberit has received a range of awards for the company’s innovative strength product design and its strong focus on sustainability product areasedit sanitary systemsedit the sanitary systems area includes installation systems cisterns faucets and flushing systems waste fittings and traps piping systemsedit this includes piping inside and outside of buildings product lines are buildingdrainage systems and supply systems bathroom ceramicsedit this encompasses toiled bowls washbasins and other complementary products like furniture showers and bathtubs notes and referencesedit  a b c d e f company description geberit businessweekcom businessweek retrieved  september    a b c d e f  annual report geberit retrieved  march    staubbisang mirjam  sustainable investments strategies sustainable investing for institutional investors risk regulations and strategies john wiley  sons p  isbn    a b c d profile